Its operation is simple and intuitive, and its modular design gives you several custom options requiring no gunsmithing
Easy to ConcealBeretta Nano

Whether you like to carry inside the waistband, on the belt or in an ankle holster, the Nano will meet and surpass your needs. At less than 1" wide and just over 5" overall length, it will disappear for ideal concealment and will not "print" thanks to its flat, low profile. Also, its organic, protrusion-free design will not dig into your body as you carry it, and its polymer frame and advanced metal coating will make it highly resistant to sweat--even on hot summer days
Personal Protection Made Easy

Nano_with_Crimson_Trace_Laser

The Nano offers you much more than an ideal concealed-carry pistol. Thanks to its modular design based on a serialized sub-chassis, it can be easily modified with different grip-frames to accommodate your preferences and even a number of accessories like laser sights. And an optional 8+1 extended magazine makes the Nano a great choice for home defense or personal protection where deep concealment is not an issue.
Easy to Use and Maintain

The Nano gives you easy assembly and disassembly, plus adjustable sights (no gunsmithing required) that allow you to always get on target even when you change ammo brands or weight. Also, the magazine-release button on the Nano can be easily reversed for left-handed use. In short, ergonomics, size, modular structure and power make the Nano the best-in-class concealed-carry and self-defense pistol. Made in USA.

title: For Sale:  BNIB: Glock 30 9 round magazine still in package
postcontent:
Call/Text me @ REDACTED if you want to come pick this up! Price is firm.

This is the infamous flush fitting 9 round magazine for the Glock 30, Glock 30SF or Glock 30S. It's BRAND NEW in the box. These were on back order for a LONG time, and mine just arrived brand new from the factory, although I regrettably sold my G30 a while ago and have no use for this magazine.

The 9 round fits flush in your gun making it much easier to carry concealed whereas the 10 round mag that comes with the G30/G30SF/G30S has the huge bulge for the mag base plate. 

Another cool thing about the 9 round mag is that you can get the Pearce pinky extension for the Glock 29 mag and it will fit on the 9 round Glock mag, yet it won't fit on the 10 round Glock mag.

Just to make clear this is ONLY for the 9 round Glock mag. No pearce extensions. I'm just including info about the G29 pinky extension because it's nice to know that it will fit on the 9 round magazine.

Below are pics of the Glock 30 with the 9 round magazine fitting flush at the bottom, and a photo of a Glock 30 with the 9 round mag with the pearce pinky extension for the G29. It looks a lot better in my opinion than the pearce pinky extension they made for the G30.

This same magazine goes on ebay for anywhere from $50-$100! What a rip off. First person with $40 gets it! Come pick it up and it's yours!

title: For Sale:  World War II Spreewerke P38 9mm
postcontent: I have a Spreewerke P38 9mm from World War II. Spreewerke was the third and final company in Germany to make this gun during the war, they were made from 1943 to 1945. The way to tell the difference between the gun by manufacturer is a three letter code stamped into the gun, "cyq" is the stamp that indicates that it is a Spreewerke and not a Walther or a Mauser. This gun looks almost brand new, especially considering it's history, along with the "cyq" stamp, there are also stamps of the German Army, the eagle over the swastika. I have seen this gun go for a wide range of prices, so my number is a shot in the dark at $600, because I have seen it go for more.
